                <h1>Understanding the Flag of England: St George's Cross</h1>
                <p>The Flag of England, known as the St George's Cross, features a red cross on a white background. It symbolizes England's patron saint, St George, and has historical roots dating back to the Middle Ages. The flag is often flown during national celebrations, sporting events, and represents English culture and pride globally.</p>
